  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the investigators project is to explore the mechanisms of pain insensitivity in
      patients with schizophrenia, in order to prevent its invalidating consequences. The
      investigators will couple methods of experimental psychology with EEG and blood samplings, in
      order to distinguish the role of non-painful perception, attention, aversive effects, and
      pain expression, and the investigators will explore an original neurobiological hypothesis
      regarding the activation of opioid receptors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
